# Final Mathematical Model

## Sets

- Workers: \( i \in W = \{1,2,3,4,5\} \)
- Tasks: \( j \in T = \{A,B,C,D\} \)

## Parameters

Let \( c_{ij} \) denote the time (hours) required for worker \( i \) to complete task \( j \):

\[
C =
\begin{bmatrix}
9 & 4 & 3 & 7 \\
4 & 6 & 5 & 6 \\
5 & 4 & 7 & 5 \\
7 & 5 & 2 & 3 \\
10 & 6 & 7 & 4
\end{bmatrix}
\]

## Decision Variables

\[
x_{ij} =
\begin{cases}
1, & \text{if worker } i \text{ is assigned to task } j \\
0, & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
\]

\[
x_{ij} \in \{0,1\}
\]

---

## Objective Function

\[
\min Z = \sum_{i \in W} \sum_{j \in T} c_{ij} x_{ij}
\]

---

## Constraints

### (1) Each task is assigned exactly one worker

\[
\sum_{i \in W} x_{ij} = 1, 
\quad \forall j \in T
\]

### (2) Each worker performs at most one task

\[
\sum_{j \in T} x_{ij} \le 1, 
\quad \forall i \in W
\]

### (3) Binary restrictions

\[
