5x_1 + 7x_2 + d_4^- &= 80 \\
3x_1 + 6x_2 + d_5^- &= 40 \\
x_1, x_2 &\ge 0 \\
d_1^\pm, d_2^\pm, d_3^-, d_4^-, d_5^- &\ge 0
\end{aligned}
\]

---

# ✅ Conclusion

- The original structure was correct.
- The refined version removes unnecessary deviation variables and presents a cleaner goal-programming formulation.
- The model is now fully consistent with:
  - No overtime
  - Weighted idle time
  - Preemptive goal priorities

This is the final optimized mathematical model suitable for Gurobi implementation.
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
from gurobipy import Model, GRB

# Create model
model = Model("Motorcycle_Goal_Programming")

# ----------------------
# Decision Variables
# ----------------------
x1 = model.addVar(lb=0, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="x1")  # Type A production
x2 = model.addVar(lb=0, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="x2")  # Type B production

# Deviation variables
d1_minus = model.addVar(lb=0, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="d1_minus")
d1_plus  = model.addVar(lb=0, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="d1_plus")

d2_minus = model.addVar(lb=0, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="d2_minus")
d2_plus  = model.addVar(lb=0, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="d2_plus")

d3_minus = model.addVar(lb=0, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="d3_minus")
d4_minus = model.addVar(lb=0, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="d4_minus")
d5_minus = model.addVar(lb=0, vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="d5_minus")

model.update()

# ----------------------
# Goal Constraints
# ----------------------

# (1) Profit goal
model.addConstr(340*x1 + 609*x2 + d1_minus - d1_plus == 3000, name="Profit_Goal")

# (2) Minimum production of Type A
model.addConstr(x1 + d2_minus - d2_plus == 5, name="TypeA_Min_Goal")

# (3) Capacity constraints (no overtime)
model.addConstr(20*x1 + d3_minus == 120, name="Manufacturing_Capacity")
model.addConstr(5*x1 + 7*x2 + d4_minus == 80, name="Assembly_Capacity")
model.addConstr(3*x1 + 6*x2 + d5_minus == 40, name="Inspection_Capacity")

# ----------------------
# Multi-objective (Preemptive Goal Programming)
# ----------------------

# Priority 1: Minimize profit shortfall
model.setObjectiveN(d1_minus, index=0, priority=3, name="Min_Profit_Shortfall")

# Priority 2: Minimize Type A production shortfall
model.setObjectiveN(d2_minus, index=1, priority=2, name="Min_TypeA_Shortfall")

# Priority 3: Minimize weighted idle time
idle_weighted = 12*d3_minus + 8*d4_minus + 10*d5_minus
model.setObjectiveN(idle_weighted, index=2, priority=1, name="Min_Weighted_Idle_Time")

# ----------------------
# Optimize
# ----------------------
model.optimize()

# ----------------------
# Output Results
# ----------------------
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print("\nOptimal Solution:")
    print(f"Type A production (x1): {x1.X}")
    print(f"Type B production (x2): {x2.X}")
    print("\nDeviation Variables:")
    print(f"d1_minus (profit shortfall): {d1_minus.X}")
    print(f"d2_minus (Type A shortfall): {d2_minus.X}")
    print(f"d3_minus (Manufacturing idle): {d3_minus.X}")
    print(f"d4_minus (Assembly idle): {d4_minus.X}")
    print(f"d5_minus (Inspection idle): {d5_minus.X}")
else:
    print("No optimal solution found.")
```
