x_{ik} =
\begin{cases}
1 & \text{if product } i \text{ is processed in position } k \\
0 & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
\]

\[
C_{kj} \ge 0 \quad \text{completion time of job at position } k \text{ on machine } j
\]

\[
C_{\max} \ge 0
\]

---

## Objective

\[
\min C_{\max}
\]

---

## Assignment Constraints (Permutation)

Each position has exactly one product:

\[
\sum_{i=1}^{3} x_{ik} = 1 \quad \forall k
\]

Each product assigned to exactly one position:

\[
\sum_{k=1}^{3} x_{ik} = 1 \quad \forall i
\]

---

## Processing Time Expression

Define processing time of job in position \(k\) on machine \(j\):

\[
P_{kj} = \sum_{i=1}^{3} t_{ij} x_{ik}
\]

---

## Flow Shop Time Constraints

### Machine 1

\[
C_{1,1} \ge P_{1,1}
\]

\[
C_{k,1} \ge C_{k-1,1} + P_{k,1}
\quad k=2,3
