A store has formulated a purchase and sales plan for a certain product from July to December. It is known that the warehouse capacity must not exceed 500 units, with 200 units in stock at the end of June. Thereafter, purchases are made at the beginning of each month. Assume the purchase and selling prices of this product for each month are shown in Table 1-21. How much should be purchased and sold each month to maximize the total revenue?

Table 1-21
| Month | 7  | 8  | 9  | 10 | 11 | 12 |
|-------|----|----|----|----|----|----|
| Buy   | 28 | 24 | 25 | 27 | 23 | 23 |
| Sell  | 29 | 24 | 26 | 28 | 22 | 25 |
-------------
【数学模型】:
 **Decision variables (for \( t = 7,\dots,12 \)):**

\[
\begin{aligned}
x_t &:= \text{quantity purchased at beginning of month } t \\
y_t &:= \text{quantity sold in month } t \\
I_t &:= \text{inventory at end of month } t
\end{aligned}
\]

---

### Parameters

Purchase price \(c_t\):

\[
\begin{aligned}
c_7=28,\; c_8=24,\; c_9=25,\; c_{10}=27,\; c_{11}=23,\; c_{12}=23
\end{aligned}
\]

Selling price \(p_t\):

\[
\begin{aligned}
p_7=29,\; p_8=24,\; p_9=26,\; p_{10}=28,\; p_{11}=22,\; p_{12}=25
\end{aligned}
\]

Initial inventory:

\[
I_6 = 200
\]

Warehouse capacity:

\[
I_t \le 500
\]

---

### Objective Function (Maximize Total Revenue)

\[
\max Z = \sum_{t=7}^{12} (p_t y_t - c_t x_t)
\]

Explicitly:

\[
\begin{aligned}
\max Z = &\; 29y_7 + 24y_8 + 26y_9 + 28y_{10} + 22y_{11} + 25y_{12} \\
&- (28x_7 + 24x_8 + 25x_9 + 27x_{10} + 23x_{11} + 23x_{12})
\end{aligned}
\]

---

### Constraints

#### 1. Inventory balance constraints

\[
I_t = I_{t-1} + x_t - y_t \qquad t=7,\dots,12
\]

Explicitly:

\[
\begin{aligned}
I_7 &= 200 + x_7 - y_7 \\
I_8 &= I_7 + x_8 - y_8 \\
I_9 &= I_8 + x_9 - y_9 \\
I_{10} &= I_9 + x_{10} - y_{10} \\
I_{11} &= I_{10} + x_{11} - y_{11} \\
I_{12} &= I_{11} + x_{12} - y_{12}
\end{aligned}
\]

---

#### 2. Warehouse capacity constraints

\[
0 \le I_t \le 500 \qquad t=7,\dots,12
\]

---

#### 3. Non-negativity constraints

\[
x_t \ge 0,\quad y_t \ge 0 \qquad t=7,\dots,12
\]

---

### Complete Linear Programming Model

\[
\begin{aligned}
\max \quad 
& \sum_{t=7}^{12} (p_t y_t - c_t x_t) \\
\text{s.t.} \quad 
& I_t = I_{t-1} + x_t - y_t \quad t=7,\dots,12 \\
& I_6 = 200 \\
& 0 \le I_t \le 500 \quad t=7,\dots,12 \\
& x_t \ge 0,\; y_t \ge 0 \quad t=7,\dots,12
\end{aligned}
\]

This is the required linear programming formulation.
【验证之后的模型】:
 The original model is essentially correct, but it can be **slightly strengthened and simplified**:

- Since inventory cannot be negative, explicitly include \( I_t \ge 0 \).
- Sales in each month cannot exceed available inventory, which is already implicitly enforced by \( I_t \ge 0 \), so no extra constraint is needed.
- The model can be written more compactly using a single indexed formulation.
- If no ending inventory requirement is specified, none is imposed.

Below is the **optimized and final linear programming model**.

---

