# Objective Function

Maximize total profit:

\[
\max Z =
\sum_{j \in \{A,B,C\}}
\left( (p_j - f_j) y_j \right)
-
\left[
2\sum_j x_{Aj}
+1.5\sum_j x_{Bj}
+1\sum_j x_{Cj}
\right]
\]

Substituting numerical values:

\[
\max Z =
2.9y_A + 2.45y_B + 1.95y_C
-2(x_{AA}+x_{AB}+x_{AC})
-1.5(x_{BA}+x_{BB}+x_{BC})
-1(x_{CA}+x_{CB}+x_{CC})
\]

Now substitute \(y_j\):

\[
\max Z =
2.9(x_{AA}+x_{BA}+x_{CA})
+2.45(x_{AB}+x_{BB}+x_{CB})
+1.95(x_{AC}+x_{BC}+x_{CC})
\]
\[
-2(x_{AA}+x_{AB}+x_{AC})
-1.5(x_{BA}+x_{BB}+x_{BC})
-1(x_{CA}+x_{CB}+x_{CC})
\]

