# ✅ Final Optimized Integer Linear Programming Model

### Decision Variables
\[
x_1 = \text{number of 10m bars cut as }(3\times3m)
\]
\[
x_2 = \text{number of 10m bars cut as }(2\times3m + 1\times4m)
\]
\[
x_3 = \text{number of 10m bars cut as }(2\times4m)
\]

---

### Objective Function (Minimize raw bars used)

\[
\min Z = x_1 + x_2 + x_3
\]

---

### Demand Constraints (Exact Satisfaction)

\[
3x_1 + 2x_2 = 90
\]

\[
x_2 + 2x_3 = 60
\]

---

### Integrality and Nonnegativity

\[
x_1, x_2, x_3 \ge 0
\]

\[
x_1, x_2, x_3 \in \mathbb{Z}
\]

---

# ✅ Final Model

\[
\begin{aligned}
\min \quad & Z = x_1 + x_2 + x_3 \\
\text{s.t.} \quad 
& 3x_1 + 2x_2 = 90 \\
& x_2 + 2x_3 = 60 \\
& x_1, x_2, x_3 \in \mathbb{Z}_{\ge 0}
\end{aligned}
\]

This is the correct and fully optimized linear integer programming formulation for the problem.
