A shoe store employs 5 full-time sales clerks and 4 part-time sales clerks. Their working hours and wage conditions are shown in Table 3.3.

Table 3.3

|  | Monthly Working Hours | Sales Volume (Pairs/Hour) | Wage (Yuan/Hour) | Overtime Pay (Yuan/Hour) |
| :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: |
| Full-time | 160 | 5 | 1 | 1.5 |
| Part-time | 80 | 2 | 0.6 | 0.7 |

Each pair of shoes sold earns a profit of 0.3 yuan. The store has set the following goals:

$p_{1}$: Achieve monthly sales of 5500 pairs;

$p_{2}$: Ensure full employment of all sales clerks;

$p_{3}$: Minimize overtime hours.

Try to establish a model for this problem.
-------------
【数学模型】:
 ### Decision Variables

Let  

\[
\begin{aligned}
&x_f = \text{regular working hours per full-time clerk (≤160)} \\
&x_p = \text{regular working hours per part-time clerk (≤80)} \\
&y_f = \text{overtime hours per full-time clerk} \\
&y_p = \text{overtime hours per part-time clerk}
\end{aligned}
\]

Total clerks:

\[
5 \text{ full-time}, \quad 4 \text{ part-time}
\]

---

### Derived Quantities

Total sales volume:

\[
S = 5(5x_f + 5y_f) + 4(2x_p + 2y_p)
\]

\[
S = 25(x_f + y_f) + 8(x_p + y_p)
\]

Total overtime hours:

\[
OT = 5y_f + 4y_p
\]

---

### Goal Programming Deviational Variables

For each goal introduce deviation variables:

\[
d_1^-, d_1^+ : \text{sales target deviation}
\]
\[
d_2^- : \text{underemployment deviation}
\]

---

### Goal Constraints

#### (1) Sales Goal \(p_1\)

Target: 5500 pairs

\[
25(x_f + y_f) + 8(x_p + y_p) + d_1^- - d_1^+ = 5500
\]

---

#### (2) Full Employment Goal \(p_2\)

Regular working hour requirements:

\[
x_f + d_{2f}^- = 160
\]
\[
x_p + d_{2p}^- = 80
\]

(Underemployment deviations \(d_{2f}^-, d_{2p}^-\))

---

#### (3) Overtime Goal \(p_3\)

\[
OT = 5y_f + 4y_p
\]

---

### Objective Function (Preemptive Goal Programming)

Priority structure:

1. \(p_1\): Achieve sales target  
2. \(p_2\): Full employment  
3. \(p_3\): Minimize overtime  

Lexicographic objective:

\[
\min Z = 
\left[
P_1: d_1^- ,
\quad
P_2: d_{2f}^- + d_{2p}^- ,
\quad
P_3: 5y_f + 4y_p
\right]
\]

---

### Nonnegativity Constraints

\[
x_f, x_p, y_f, y_p \ge 0
\]

\[
d_1^-, d_1^+, d_{2f}^-, d_{2p}^- \ge 0
\]

---

### Complete Linear Goal Programming Model

\[
\begin{aligned}
\min & \quad [P_1:d_1^-,\; P_2:d_{2f}^-+d_{2p}^-,\; P_3:5y_f+4y_p] \\
\text{s.t.} 
& 25(x_f+y_f)+8(x_p+y_p)+d_1^- - d_1^+ = 5500 \\
& x_f + d_{2f}^- = 160 \\
& x_p + d_{2p}^- = 80 \\
& x_f,x_p,y_f,y_p,d_1^-,d_1^+,d_{2f}^-,d_{2p}^- \ge 0
\end{aligned}
\]

This is the required linear goal programming model.
【验证之后的模型】:
 The previous model has **structural errors**:

1. It incorrectly models working hours *per clerk* instead of total hours.  
2. Full employment is wrongly written as an equality on a single worker.  
3. Wage and profit structure is ignored (though not strictly required for goal programming, hours must be correctly modeled).  
4. Regular-hour upper bounds were not enforced properly.  

Below is the **corrected and optimized preemptive goal programming model**.

---

# ✅ Correct Mathematical Model

---

## 1. Decision Variables

\[
\begin{aligned}
&x_f = \text{total regular hours of all full-time clerks} \\
&x_p = \text{total regular hours of all part-time clerks} \\
&y_f = \text{total overtime hours of all full-time clerks} \\
&y_p = \text{total overtime hours of all part-time clerks}
\end{aligned}
\]

Deviation variables:

\[
d_1^-, d_1^+ \quad (\text{sales goal})
\]
\[
d_2^- \quad (\text{underemployment})
\]

---

## 2. Basic Data

Maximum regular hours:

\[
x_f \le 5 \times 160 = 800
\]

\[
x_p \le 4 \times 80 = 320
\]

Sales productivity:

\[
\text{Full-time: } 5 \text{ pairs/hour}
\]

\[
\text{Part-time: } 2 \text{ pairs/hour}
\]

---

## 3. Goal Constraints

### (1) Sales Goal \(p_1\)

Target: 5500 pairs

\[
5(x_f + y_f) + 2(x_p + y_p) + d_1^- - d_1^+ = 5500
\]

---

### (2) Full Employment Goal \(p_2\)

All regular hours should be fully used:

\[
x_f + x_p + d_2^- = 800 + 320 = 1120
\]

(Only underemployment deviation is penalized.)

---

### (3) Overtime Goal \(p_3\)

Total overtime:

\[
OT = y_f + y_p
\]

---

## 4. System Constraints

\[
x_f \le 800
\]

\[
x_p \le 320
\]

\[
x_f,x_p,y_f,y_p \ge 0
\]

\[
d_1^-,d_1^+,d_2^- \ge 0
\]

---

## 5. Preemptive Goal Programming Objective

Priority structure:

1. \(P_1\): Minimize sales shortfall  
2. \(P_2\): Minimize underemployment  
3. \(P_3\): Minimize overtime  

Lexicographic objective:

\[
\min Z =
\left[
P_1: d_1^-,
\quad
P_2: d_2^-,
\quad
P_3: y_f + y_p
\right]
\]

---

# ✅ Final Compact Model

\[
\begin{aligned}
\min & \quad [P_1:d_1^-,\; P_2:d_2^-,\; P_3:y_f+y_p] \\
\text{s.t.} 
& 5(x_f+y_f)+2(x_p+y_p)+d_1^- - d_1^+ = 5500 \\
& x_f + x_p + d_2^- = 1120 \\
& x_f \le 800 \\
& x_p \le 320 \\
& x_f,x_p,y_f,y_p,d_1^-,d_1^+,d_2^- \ge 0
\end{aligned}
\]

---

### ✅ Improvements Made
- Correct aggregation of total working hours  
- Correct full-employment modeling  
- Removed redundant variables  
- Simplified structure for direct Gurobi implementation  
- Fully linear and scalable  

---

If needed, I can next convert this directly into **standard weighted goal programming form** suitable for single-objective Gurobi implementation.
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
import gurobipy as gp
from gurobipy import GRB

# Create model
model = gp.Model("ShoeStore_GoalProgramming")

# Decision variables
x_f = model.addVar(lb=0, ub=800, name="x_f")   # regular hours full-time
x_p = model.addVar(lb=0, ub=320, name="x_p")   # regular hours part-time
y_f = model.addVar(lb=0, name="y_f")           # overtime hours full-time
y_p = model.addVar(lb=0, name="y_p")           # overtime hours part-time

# Deviation variables
d1_minus = model.addVar(lb=0, name="d1_minus")
d1_plus  = model.addVar(lb=0, name="d1_plus")
d2_minus = model.addVar(lb=0, name="d2_minus")

# Goal constraints

# (1) Sales goal
model.addConstr(
    5 * (x_f + y_f) + 2 * (x_p + y_p) + d1_minus - d1_plus == 5500,
    name="SalesGoal"
)

# (2) Full employment goal
model.addConstr(
    x_f + x_p + d2_minus == 1120,
    name="FullEmploymentGoal"
)

# Set hierarchical (lexicographic) objectives

# Priority 1: Minimize sales shortfall
model.setObjectiveN(d1_minus, index=0, priority=3, name="Minimize_Sales_Shortfall")

# Priority 2: Minimize underemployment
model.setObjectiveN(d2_minus, index=1, priority=2, name="Minimize_Underemployment")

# Priority 3: Minimize overtime
model.setObjectiveN(y_f + y_p, index=2, priority=1, name="Minimize_Overtime")

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print("Optimal Solution Found:\n")
    print(f"Regular hours (Full-time): {x_f.X}")
    print(f"Regular hours (Part-time): {x_p.X}")
    print(f"Overtime hours (Full-time): {y_f.X}")
    print(f"Overtime hours (Part-time): {y_p.X}")
    print(f"Sales shortfall (d1_minus): {d1_minus.X}")
    print(f"Sales surplus (d1_plus): {d1_plus.X}")
    print(f"Underemployment (d2_minus): {d2_minus.X}")
else:
    print("No optimal solution found.")
```
